<div class="pb-3">
  <div class="gradient">
    <h2 class="pb-1">WORKING EXPERIENCES</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Here are some of my key work experiences, ranging from web development to other software-related roles.
    </p>
  </div>

  @* FIRST JOB*@
  <div class="card-top pt-3 pb-2 pe-4 ps-4 mb-4">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
        <p class="h4">Fanderlust - C#/.NET Developer</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-start text-md-end">
        <p class="date">09/2024 - NOW</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      I developed a <strong>web application</strong> that acts as a marketplace for sports ticket buyers and sellers.
      Instead of direct transactions, the platform connects customers with a dedicated team that finds tickets on their
      behalf.
      The application is built using <strong>C# with .NET and Razor Pages</strong> for a smooth user experience.
    </p>
    <p>Key contributions:</p>
    <ul class="circle">
      <li>
        Developed a <strong>secure login system</strong> with external authentication (Google).
      </li>
      <li>
        Implemented <strong>reCAPTCHA W3</strong> for enhanced security against bot attacks.
      </li>
      <li>
        Designed a <strong>user-friendly interface</strong> for buyers to submit requests and interact with the team.
      </li>
      <li>
        Built a <strong>scalable backend</strong> using <strong>.NET and Razor Pages</strong> for performance and
        maintainability.
      </li>
      <li>
        Future implementation plans include <strong>AWS integration</strong> for cloud scalability.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This project strengthened my skills in <strong>C#, .NET, security best practices, and full-stack
        development</strong>,
      while also giving me experience in building secure and scalable marketplace applications.
    </p>
  </div>

  @* SECOND JOB*@
  <div class="card-top pt-3 pb-2 pe-4 ps-4 mb-4">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
        <p class="h4">Sports Ticket Management SaaS - Node.js Developer</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-start text-md-end">
        <p class="date">08/2024 - 09/2024</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>
      I developed a SaaS platform for managing sports event tickets, enabling users to manually input ticket data and
      track sales and revenue efficiently.
      This system helps event organizers monitor ticket allocations and financial performance in a structured way.
    </p>
    <p>Key contributions:</p>
    <ul class="circle">
      <li>
        Built the backend using <strong>Node.js</strong> and <strong>Express</strong> for scalability.
      </li>
      <li>
        Implemented <strong>role-based authentication</strong> for secure access.
      </li>
      <li>
        Designed a database (<strong>MongoDB/MySQL</strong>) to store ticket records and revenue tracking.
      </li>
      <li>
        Developed a <strong>dashboard</strong> for real-time monitoring of sales and earnings.
      </li>
      <li>
        Optimized performance for multi-user and multi-event scenarios.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This project enhanced my expertise in <strong>backend development, SaaS architecture, and database
        management</strong>
      while improving my ability to build scalable and data-driven applications.
    </p>
  </div>

